WEBVTT

00:00.746 --> 00:03.313
<i>Jack: Over 68 million Americans</i>

00:03.347 --> 00:06.149
<i>leave the safety of our
borders every year.</i>

00:06.183 --> 00:07.817
<i>If danger strikes,</i>

00:07.852 --> 00:10.620
<i>the FBI's international response team</i>

00:10.654 --> 00:12.355
<i>is called into action.</i>

00:13.591 --> 00:16.359
♪

00:21.899 --> 00:24.334
<i>♪ La gente quiere un bailazo ♪</i>

00:24.368 --> 00:26.669
<i>♪ cada noche es un bailazo</i>

00:26.704 --> 00:29.139
<i>♪ zapata vive un bailazo</i>

00:29.173 --> 00:31.908
<i>♪ baila, revolucionario</i>

00:31.942 --> 00:34.711
<i>♪ manos pa'rriba que es un asalto ♪</i>

00:34.745 --> 00:36.813
This is the best trip, ever.

00:36.847 --> 00:38.214
You say that every year.

00:38.249 --> 00:40.417
I didn't say it when Dad
got stung by a jellyfish.

00:40.451 --> 00:42.752
- [Laughs]
- You did after the hotel doctor

00:42.787 --> 00:43.920
took us all in his catamaran.

00:43.954 --> 00:45.422
That was awesome.

00:45.456 --> 00:46.689
What about you, Mom?

00:46.724 --> 00:48.691
What's your favorite vacation down here?

00:48.726 --> 00:49.859
- [Tearfully]
- I don't know, honey.

00:49.894 --> 00:51.394
They're all special,

00:51.429 --> 00:52.862
'cause your dad and I
shared them with you two.

00:52.897 --> 00:53.897
[Chuckle]

00:53.931 --> 00:55.732
Let's toast, hm?

00:55.766 --> 00:57.367
To our last night in paradise

00:57.401 --> 00:59.536
and, uh, to

00:59.570 --> 01:00.737
I already booked this
place for next year.

01:00.771 --> 01:02.205
- [Laughter]
- Yeah!

01:02.239 --> 01:03.573
You know what's really gonna make this

01:03.607 --> 01:05.007
the best trip, ever?

01:05.042 --> 01:07.710
One Direction's free concert tonight.

01:07.745 --> 01:10.380
Oh, my god! I love this place!

01:10.414 --> 01:12.615
Hey, guys, we called. There
is no concert tonight.

01:12.650 --> 01:14.684
- But it says so right there.
- Yeah, I know.

01:14.718 --> 01:15.952
But the flyer's just a prank.

01:15.986 --> 01:17.454
Today is... what did the guy call it?

01:17.488 --> 01:19.355
<i>Día de los Inocentes.</i>

01:19.390 --> 01:20.690
<i>Día de los Inocentes,</i>

01:20.724 --> 01:22.692
which means today is
like April fools' day.

01:22.726 --> 01:23.960
Wow.

01:23.994 --> 01:25.361
That seriously sucks...

01:25.396 --> 01:26.763
Ryan! Language.

01:26.797 --> 01:28.598
Look, I know it's very disappointing,

01:28.632 --> 01:30.867
but I say we finish up dinner here

01:30.901 --> 01:32.735
and then we all head back to town

01:32.770 --> 01:33.903
and ransack the place for souvenirs.

01:33.938 --> 01:35.638
What do you say? Who's with me?

01:35.673 --> 01:37.574
Hm?

01:37.608 --> 01:38.975
Go inside and wash up.

01:39.009 --> 01:40.610
Dad will take you to the boardwalk.

01:40.644 --> 01:41.911
Okay.

01:43.447 --> 01:44.747
You're not coming with us?

01:44.782 --> 01:46.349
No, I'm exhausted.

01:48.419 --> 01:49.719
We shouldn't have come.

01:49.753 --> 01:50.920
It's just gonna make it harder.

01:56.660 --> 01:57.694
[Crickets chirp]

02:05.870 --> 02:08.937
♪

02:11.876 --> 02:15.311
[Eerie music plays]

02:20.151 --> 02:22.085
- [Whispering]
- Daniel.

02:22.119 --> 02:23.219
Daniel.

02:24.855 --> 02:25.955
- [Gasp]
- Unh!

02:28.192 --> 02:30.860
[Ring]

02:30.895 --> 02:32.595
Good morning. Thank you for calling.

02:32.630 --> 02:34.197
<i>Daniel: Help! Something
happened to my wife.</i>

02:34.231 --> 02:35.298
<i>There's blood.</i>

02:35.332 --> 02:37.167
I was in the den. I woke up

02:37.201 --> 02:39.135
and went to check on my wife. Oh, God.

02:39.170 --> 02:41.504
Mr. Wolf, I'd like to suggest
we move your children back

02:41.539 --> 02:43.373
to the main building for both
their safety and comfort.

02:43.407 --> 02:45.708
- Dad, we wanna stay with you.
- Where's Mommy?!

02:45.743 --> 02:46.976
We're gonna find her, honey.

02:47.011 --> 02:48.511
Just go with this lady, okay?

02:48.546 --> 02:50.513
I'll be right there. I'm
just gonna look for Mommy.

02:52.750 --> 02:54.651
[Suspenseful music plays]

02:58.856 --> 03:00.557
We need to call the police.
Have you called the police yet?

03:00.591 --> 03:02.225
We've notified the authorities.
They're on their way.

03:02.259 --> 03:04.294
But, please, Mr. Wolf, I
need you to remain calm.

03:04.328 --> 03:07.697
Calm?! My wife is gone! There's...
there's blood!

03:07.731 --> 03:08.998
We're wasting time!

03:09.033 --> 03:10.567
- Jessica!
- Señora Wolf!

03:10.601 --> 03:13.369
- Jessica!
- Señora Wolf! Señora Wolf!

03:13.404 --> 03:15.004
Jessica!

03:15.039 --> 03:16.673
Jes-si-ca!

03:16.707 --> 03:19.142
- [Suspenseful music climbs]
- [Chime]

03:25.749 --> 03:26.916
Whatcha readin'?

03:26.951 --> 03:29.252
"And then there were none."

03:29.286 --> 03:30.753
Why, you lose a bet?

03:30.788 --> 03:33.323
Agatha Christie mystery.

03:33.357 --> 03:34.857
Is that the one where the judge does it?

03:34.892 --> 03:36.259
He kills everybody and then,

03:36.293 --> 03:37.694
he shoots himself in the head,

03:37.728 --> 03:40.997
leaving this red mark,
like the mark of Cain.

03:41.031 --> 03:43.700
Well, so much for my
in-flight entertainment.

03:43.734 --> 03:46.769
Sorry, guys. Looks we are
not going home, after all.

03:46.804 --> 03:47.770
We caught another case.

03:47.805 --> 03:51.574
Puerta de Santos, México.

03:51.609 --> 03:53.243
You gonna be all right with this?

03:53.277 --> 03:56.112
Yeah, why wouldn't I be?

03:56.146 --> 03:57.347
Just wanna make sure.

03:57.381 --> 03:59.882
It's Mexico.

03:59.917 --> 04:02.885
Well, it's a big country, Jack.

04:02.920 --> 04:04.587
Yes, it is, it's a big country

04:04.622 --> 04:06.889
I know you've been deliberately avoiding

04:06.924 --> 04:10.426
since Brad's death.

04:10.461 --> 04:11.761
Look, I appreciate your concern.

04:11.795 --> 04:13.029
I really do.

04:13.063 --> 04:15.565
But, now, I'm back in the IRT

04:15.599 --> 04:16.632
and, the fact of the matter is

04:16.666 --> 04:20.702
I was bound to face this
situation, sooner or later.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.806
You know we have your back, always?

04:23.841 --> 04:25.074
Mm, that's why I'm gonna be all right.

04:27.344 --> 04:28.778
<i>Hola, mis amigos.</i>

04:28.812 --> 04:30.480
<i>Here's news from south of the border,</i>

04:30.514 --> 04:31.881
<i>down Mexico way.</i>

04:31.915 --> 04:33.750
<i>Jessica Wolf, age 36,</i>

04:33.784 --> 04:35.151
<i>a graphic designer from
Fort Worth, Texas,</i>

04:35.185 --> 04:37.487
<i>is on vacation with
her husband, Daniel,</i>

04:37.521 --> 04:39.822
<i>a management consultant;
And their two kids:</i>

04:39.857 --> 04:41.924
<i>Ryan, 11; and Megan, 9.</i>

04:41.959 --> 04:43.826
They're staying at a beachfront villa

04:43.861 --> 04:46.929
<i>at the Las Casitas del Pacifico resort.</i>

04:46.964 --> 04:48.965
<i>At 4:12 am local time,</i>

04:48.999 --> 04:50.900
<i>Daniel reported his
wife, Jessica, missing.</i>

04:50.934 --> 04:52.902
<i>There were indications of violence,</i>

04:52.936 --> 04:55.438
<i>and $4,000 worth of jewelry
was stolen, however,</i>

04:55.472 --> 04:58.107
<i>a canvas of the resort's
property turned up nothing.</i>

04:58.142 --> 05:00.677
Then, at 11:47 am,

05:00.711 --> 05:02.645
<i>a body washed ashore at Cobra Cove,</i>

05:02.680 --> 05:04.781
<i>about 5 miles south of Las Casitas.</i>

05:04.815 --> 05:08.117
Jessica Wolf was a U.S. citizen
murdered on Mexican soil,

05:08.152 --> 05:10.820
so, our consulate general in Juarez

05:10.854 --> 05:12.355
has requested the IRT's help

05:12.389 --> 05:14.357
with the impending
homicide investigation.

05:14.391 --> 05:16.125
Which won't be made any
easier by the fact that

05:16.160 --> 05:18.127
Puerta de Santos does not
have a police force.

05:18.162 --> 05:20.697
Usually, resorts like Las Casitas

05:20.731 --> 05:22.932
enlist the service of a
private security firm.

05:22.966 --> 05:25.201
In this case, it's a U.S.-based company

05:25.235 --> 05:27.337
called PLN International.

05:27.371 --> 05:30.006
They secured the villa
and the beach site

05:30.040 --> 05:31.541
until the Mexican
federal police arrived

05:31.575 --> 05:33.276
and they are on the scene now.

05:33.310 --> 05:34.444
Mae: We can't tell much
from these photos,

05:34.478 --> 05:36.512
but the sheets that are
wrapped around Jessica's body

05:36.547 --> 05:38.181
look like a crude
forensic countermeasure,

05:38.215 --> 05:40.316
a way to spirit a body off the grounds

05:40.351 --> 05:41.718
without raising much suspicion.

05:41.752 --> 05:43.486
Well, if $4,000 in jewelry was taken,

05:43.520 --> 05:45.688
then, burglary could've
been a primary motive.

05:45.723 --> 05:47.957
Jessica's murder could've
been an impulsive act.

05:47.991 --> 05:49.959
Yeah, but don't you think
breaking into a hotel villa

05:49.993 --> 05:51.994
in the middle of the night
is a pretty provocative act,

05:52.029 --> 05:53.996
even for a desperate burglar?

05:54.031 --> 05:56.132
It's possible Jessica was targeted.

05:56.166 --> 05:57.967
- What do you think?
- I'd like to know

05:58.001 --> 05:59.902
where Daniel Wolf was
when all this went down.

05:59.937 --> 06:01.170
Where were his kids?

06:01.205 --> 06:03.339
- What did they see and hear?
<i>- I wish I could tell you, but,</i>

06:03.374 --> 06:04.741
<i>aside from his initial statement,</i>

06:04.775 --> 06:06.075
<i>Daniel stopped cooperating with police</i>

06:06.110 --> 06:07.176
<i>as soon as his children were taken</i>

06:07.211 --> 06:09.045
<i>into protective custody
as material witnesses.</i>

06:09.079 --> 06:11.848
Our job now is to get down
there and assist the MFP

06:11.882 --> 06:14.183
while also protecting
Daniel's civil rights,

06:14.218 --> 06:16.085
regardless of his guilt or innocence.

06:16.120 --> 06:17.720
<i>Not to rush to judgment, boss,</i>

06:17.755 --> 06:18.788
<i>but what I just dug up on this guy</i>

06:18.822 --> 06:20.757
<i>is straight out of the
shady-husband playbook.</i>

06:20.791 --> 06:21.958
- <i>Take a look.
- [Beep]</i>

06:21.992 --> 06:25.027
A year ago, Daniel's consulting
firm filed for bankruptcy.

06:25.062 --> 06:27.563
Eight months later, Jessica
filed for divorce,

06:27.598 --> 06:30.066
and then she withdrew the
filing a month later.

06:30.100 --> 06:32.235
<i>But here's the kicker: 30 days ago,</i>

06:32.269 --> 06:34.170
<i>Daniel took out an insurance
policy on his wife,</i>

06:34.204 --> 06:35.938
<i>so, now, this dude is
line to collect...</i>

06:35.973 --> 06:37.707
<i>wait for it...</i>

06:37.741 --> 06:39.842
<i>- $1 million.
- [Whistle]</i>

06:39.877 --> 06:41.911
The fact is that the only
way we're gonna know

06:41.945 --> 06:44.547
if Daniel Wolf is playing
the grieving husband

06:44.581 --> 06:47.049
is by getting down there and
talkin' to him face-to-face.

06:47.084 --> 06:48.718
Well, what if he refuses to talk to us?

06:48.752 --> 06:51.053
What if he refuses to
talk to the only people

06:51.088 --> 06:55.391
who can protect his best
interests, his civil rights?

06:55.426 --> 06:58.027
Well, that'll tell us something
about him, then, won't it?

