07:22.572 --> 07:24.839
<i>Clara: "Perfect order is the forerunner</i>

07:24.873 --> 07:26.607
<i>to perfect horror."</i>

07:26.642 --> 07:28.175
<i>Carlos Fuentes.</i>

07:28.210 --> 07:30.478
[Guitar plays]

07:35.150 --> 07:37.084
Unit Chief Garrett.

07:37.119 --> 07:38.753
I'm Consul General Patrick Hillis.

07:38.787 --> 07:40.187
It's a pleasure to meet you.

07:40.222 --> 07:42.456
This is Mr. Raymond Wright.
He's representing

07:42.491 --> 07:43.858
Daniel Wolf and his family.

07:43.892 --> 07:45.159
Good to meet you. This is my team...

07:45.193 --> 07:47.461
Look, I'm sorry, but,
pleasantries aside,

07:47.496 --> 07:48.963
I'm deeply concerned that every moment

07:48.997 --> 07:51.265
the MFP is focused on
my client as a suspect

07:51.299 --> 07:53.467
is a moment wasted on
finding the real killer.

07:53.502 --> 07:55.302
Mr. Wright, please. The IRT...

07:55.337 --> 07:57.672
Can't change the fact
that the crime scenes

07:57.706 --> 07:59.607
have been compromised
by hotel employees

07:59.641 --> 08:00.741
and can't change the fact that

08:00.776 --> 08:03.811
expediency trumps justice in
the Mexican legal system.

08:03.845 --> 08:05.980
I thought it was my
youth and inexperience

08:06.014 --> 08:06.781
that was the problem.

08:06.815 --> 08:08.716
Just getting to that, Miss Ruiz.

08:08.750 --> 08:13.354
That's Chief Inspector
Ruiz to you, Señor Wright.

08:13.388 --> 08:15.456
- To all of you.
- Unit Chief Garrett.

08:15.490 --> 08:18.225
Agents Seger, Simmons, and Jarvis.

08:18.260 --> 08:20.461
Look, I won't lie to you.

08:20.495 --> 08:21.629
I don't want you here.

08:21.663 --> 08:24.565
This is my case and you being
here complicates my life

08:24.599 --> 08:26.300
and I don't like complications.

08:26.334 --> 08:28.536
I like everything <i>muy fácil.</i>

08:28.570 --> 08:31.405
But my bosses in the capital
think that the FBI's cooperation

08:31.440 --> 08:34.140
will help me, so, please, follow me.

08:41.183 --> 08:44.952
Man: <i>Hombres, necesito
en la playa ahora.</i>

08:47.389 --> 08:51.258
CI Ruiz, are you the only
officer assigned to this case?

08:51.293 --> 08:52.993
See? This is what I'm talking about.

08:53.028 --> 08:55.429
Mr. Wright, I understand your
concern, but, right now,

08:55.464 --> 08:56.564
you need to be seen, not heard.

08:56.598 --> 08:59.734
Yes, I'm the only MPF officer
assigned to this case,

08:59.768 --> 09:01.569
but my bosses gave me permission

09:01.603 --> 09:03.571
to deputize the Las
Casitas security staff.

09:03.605 --> 09:05.106
They're U.S.-trained, so probably

09:05.140 --> 09:07.675
a whole lot better than
MFP, don't you think?

09:07.709 --> 09:09.243
So, how do you think somebody managed

09:09.277 --> 09:10.845
to take Jessica Wolf off the property

09:10.879 --> 09:11.912
without bein' picked up on one

09:11.947 --> 09:14.348
- of these security cameras?
- That's a good question.

09:14.382 --> 09:16.584
Jessica's killer knows
the lay of the land.

09:16.618 --> 09:18.419
And your client fits that description.

09:18.453 --> 09:19.620
He needs to start
answering my questions.

09:19.654 --> 09:21.789
He'll answer questions when
you let him see his children.

09:21.823 --> 09:23.457
His children are material witnesses.

09:23.492 --> 09:24.525
They're scared, so
they haven't talked...

09:24.559 --> 09:26.260
of course they're scared.
They lost their mother

09:26.294 --> 09:27.595
and their father's
being kept from them.

09:27.629 --> 09:29.029
Hold on. I have a solution here.

09:29.064 --> 09:31.432
Agent Seger has years of expertise

09:31.466 --> 09:33.467
taking witness statements from minors.

09:33.502 --> 09:35.536
She'll be able to put
the children at ease

09:35.570 --> 09:37.271
and get to the truth.

09:37.305 --> 09:40.741
I also think Daniel might be
more comfortable talkin' to me.

09:40.776 --> 09:42.243
Daniel will agree to that.

09:42.277 --> 09:44.445
Like I said,

09:44.479 --> 09:46.447
<i>muy fácil.</i>

09:46.481 --> 09:47.648
One of you is a coroner, right?

09:47.682 --> 09:48.716
A medical examiner, yes.

09:48.750 --> 09:50.451
We were going to transport
the body to Mexico city

09:50.485 --> 09:52.620
for an autopsy. Could you do it here?

09:52.654 --> 09:54.088
They don't just bring me along

09:54.122 --> 09:56.490
for my good taste and
my sense of humor.

09:56.525 --> 09:58.893
I'd like Agent Simmons to walk
through the villa crime scene.

09:58.927 --> 10:01.762
I have no problem with that,
as long as I get to chaperone.

10:01.797 --> 10:03.164
Okay.

10:03.198 --> 10:06.133
Let's go to work.

10:06.168 --> 10:07.635
So you're with the FBI?

10:07.669 --> 10:09.370
Yes. I'm here to help, Daniel.

10:14.309 --> 10:17.144
They found Jessica. They
won't let me see her.

10:17.179 --> 10:18.345
Won't even let me see my own kids.

10:18.380 --> 10:20.347
What the hell's wrong with these people?

10:20.382 --> 10:22.616
I know this is difficult,
but the best way

10:22.651 --> 10:24.018
to help yourself nd your family is

10:24.052 --> 10:25.386
to just talk to me.

10:28.623 --> 10:29.924
Where were you last night?

10:29.958 --> 10:31.592
Jessica wasn't feeling well.

10:31.626 --> 10:32.993
She wanted to stay in the villa

10:33.028 --> 10:36.697
while I took the kids souvenir hunting.

10:36.731 --> 10:37.965
We got back late, after midnight.

10:39.634 --> 10:41.101
Kids crashed on the couch.

10:41.136 --> 10:43.838
I didn't want to disturb Jessica, so,

10:43.872 --> 10:45.639
I went to the den, fell asleep.

10:45.674 --> 10:46.774
I woke up at 4:00.

10:46.808 --> 10:48.542
I checked on her.

10:48.577 --> 10:50.511
And that's...

10:50.545 --> 10:52.346
that's when I found the blood

10:52.380 --> 10:53.848
and jewelry box tossed on the floor.

10:53.882 --> 10:55.983
I-I called for help.

10:56.017 --> 10:59.520
Nobody told me there's no
police in this damn town

10:59.554 --> 11:02.189
and that it'd take an hour
for them to get here.

11:02.224 --> 11:03.991
All that wasted time.

11:04.025 --> 11:05.392
Did you account for every guard

11:05.427 --> 11:07.394
who was present at this scene?

11:07.429 --> 11:09.196
Did you take their prints as exemplars?

11:09.231 --> 11:11.632
Like I said, all
well-trained in the U.S.

11:11.666 --> 11:12.800
They know how to fill out

11:12.834 --> 11:14.335
the correct incident reports.

11:14.369 --> 11:15.903
Well, they don't know how
to preserve a crime scene

11:15.937 --> 11:17.705
or collect evidence.

11:17.739 --> 11:19.874
You know, as well as I do
this scene is compromised.

11:19.908 --> 11:22.042
Agent Simmons, you
know, as well as I do

11:22.077 --> 11:24.678
your rules of evidence
aren't the same as mine.

11:24.713 --> 11:27.014
Besides, saved the best for last.

11:27.048 --> 11:29.083
[Eerie music plays]

11:29.117 --> 11:30.751
Well, that looks like

11:30.785 --> 11:32.686
at least 2 liters of blood.

11:32.721 --> 11:34.188
Maybe 3.

11:34.222 --> 11:35.890
A lethal loss of blood.

11:35.924 --> 11:37.725
Jessica wasn't just assaulted here.

11:37.759 --> 11:39.693
She died in this room
and someone tried,

11:39.728 --> 11:41.095
not so good, to cover it up,

11:41.129 --> 11:43.731
make it look like a
burglary gone wrong.

11:43.765 --> 11:44.865
May I look at your cellphone?

11:44.900 --> 11:45.933
What?

11:45.967 --> 11:47.601
Your cellphone. May I see it?

11:47.636 --> 11:49.436
Why?

11:49.471 --> 11:51.705
Well, it may have digital
information on it

11:51.740 --> 11:53.340
that could support your alibi.

11:53.375 --> 11:56.777
I-I lost it.

11:56.811 --> 11:58.679
Somewhere out there, on the beach,

11:58.713 --> 12:02.383
during the search.

12:02.417 --> 12:03.918
Look.

12:03.952 --> 12:06.253
I'm here to help you, Daniel.

12:06.288 --> 12:08.389
But I know your consulting
firm went bankrupt,

12:08.423 --> 12:10.457
I know Jessica filed for divorce,

12:10.492 --> 12:11.792
and I know she's now worth

12:11.826 --> 12:13.694
a million dollars, now that she's dead,

12:13.728 --> 12:15.863
so I need you to tell me the truth.

12:19.234 --> 12:21.735
I didn't kill my wife.

12:25.840 --> 12:28.609
Houston, we have a problem.

12:28.643 --> 12:30.444
In prepping the body for autopsy,

12:30.478 --> 12:32.980
somebody was kind enough
to remove those sheets

12:33.014 --> 12:34.882
that were wrapped around her body.

12:34.916 --> 12:36.817
They shouldn't have done that.

12:36.851 --> 12:41.488
Note to file: Must
find missing evidence.

12:41.523 --> 12:43.257
All right, Jess.

12:43.291 --> 12:44.792
Help me help you.

12:51.499 --> 12:53.767
Victim sustained several
defensive wounds

12:53.802 --> 12:56.070
during the attack,

12:56.104 --> 12:57.838
including a severe incised wound

12:57.872 --> 12:59.340
to the palmar surface of both hands,

12:59.374 --> 13:01.141
indicating that she grasped
the blade of the weapon

13:01.176 --> 13:02.843
during the attack.

13:02.877 --> 13:04.278
She fought.

13:04.312 --> 13:05.679
Cause of death is exsanguination,

13:05.714 --> 13:07.848
due to a single sharp-force injury,

13:07.882 --> 13:10.084
severing the ascending aorta.

13:10.118 --> 13:13.120
The remaining 46 penetrating
sharp-force injuries

13:13.154 --> 13:14.655
were administered postmortem,

13:14.689 --> 13:17.324
indicative of the assailant's
acute aggression,

13:17.359 --> 13:19.426
usually referred to as overkill

13:19.461 --> 13:22.930
and typically a sign that
the attack was personal.

13:25.133 --> 13:28.435
Ryan, Megan, you don't
have to talk to me,

13:28.470 --> 13:29.636
or anyone.

13:29.671 --> 13:31.672
I just wanna make sure you're safe.

13:31.706 --> 13:32.840
You guys hungry?

13:36.911 --> 13:38.679
Do me a favor and order me a pizza.

13:38.713 --> 13:40.781
Yes, Ma'am.

13:40.815 --> 13:42.349
So, food is on the way.

13:42.384 --> 13:43.650
Okay?

13:43.685 --> 13:44.885
Thank you.

13:44.919 --> 13:46.653
You're welcome.

13:46.688 --> 13:48.756
You need anything else, you
let me know, all right?

13:51.926 --> 13:53.293
Did Daddy hurt Mommy?

13:53.328 --> 13:57.898
[Melancholy tune plays]

13:57.932 --> 14:01.335
Why would you ask that?

14:01.369 --> 14:03.871
Mom and Dad, they just yelled.

14:06.041 --> 14:07.007
A lot.

14:07.042 --> 14:08.409
Just on this trip,

14:08.443 --> 14:09.710
or were they fighting before that?

14:09.744 --> 14:12.346
For a long time, but, we hoped this trip

14:12.380 --> 14:13.714
would make it better.

14:13.748 --> 14:15.215
It wasn't.

14:17.952 --> 14:19.053
It was just weird that

14:19.087 --> 14:22.423
they were pretending like
nothing was going on and...

14:22.457 --> 14:26.493
Like we didn't know
something was going on.

14:26.528 --> 14:28.395
It was so stupid.

14:28.430 --> 14:30.564
Did you ever see your father

14:30.598 --> 14:32.533
be rough with your mother?

14:36.871 --> 14:38.238
You think you can tell me

14:38.273 --> 14:40.274
what you remember from last night?

14:40.308 --> 14:43.410
I don't remember much, just...

14:43.445 --> 14:45.712
Dad woke us up.

14:45.747 --> 14:46.914
Mom wasn't there.

14:49.217 --> 14:50.751
What about you, Ryan?

14:50.785 --> 14:53.887
I-I remember

14:53.922 --> 14:55.689
my father.

14:55.723 --> 14:58.392
<i>Jessica: Daniel. Daniel.</i>

14:58.426 --> 15:04.031
Standing over me. It was weird and...

15:04.065 --> 15:07.401
and I fell asleep again,
and, like Meg said,

15:07.435 --> 15:08.869
Dad woke us up.

15:11.673 --> 15:13.607
Mom was gone.

15:13.641 --> 15:14.741
Okay.

15:17.479 --> 15:20.280
Look, this is me, trying very hard

15:20.315 --> 15:21.548
to extend professional courtesy

15:21.583 --> 15:23.951
to fellow law enforcement,
but I'm not here

15:23.985 --> 15:25.953
to ask for permission
to arrest Daniel Wolf.

15:25.987 --> 15:28.789
Well, thank you for
your courtesy, CI Ruiz.

15:28.823 --> 15:30.424
It's just that I've had the chance

15:30.458 --> 15:32.993
to speak with Daniel and
compare notes with my team

15:33.027 --> 15:34.328
and there are a few

15:34.362 --> 15:36.163
psychological inconsistencies here.

15:36.197 --> 15:37.598
Is that right?

15:37.632 --> 15:40.067
Take Daniel's expression
of love for his children.

15:40.101 --> 15:41.969
It's genuine. It's very telling.

15:42.003 --> 15:43.904
His behavior totally contradicts

15:43.938 --> 15:45.172
my all-in theory.

15:45.206 --> 15:46.340
All-in theory?

15:46.374 --> 15:48.408
Patriarchs who murder their wives

15:48.443 --> 15:49.776
with their own children present

15:49.811 --> 15:52.446
usually feel compelled to go all-in,

15:52.480 --> 15:54.982
killing the whole family,
including themselves.

15:55.016 --> 15:57.818
Patriarchs perceive it as
an act of love and mercy.

15:57.852 --> 15:59.453
That didn't happen here. Why?

15:59.487 --> 16:00.587
<i>Hijos de la fregada.</i>

16:00.622 --> 16:02.322
How can you look at evidence
right in front of your face

16:02.357 --> 16:04.258
- and not even see it?!
- With all due respect,

16:04.292 --> 16:06.827
the evidence in this
case is circumstantial.

16:06.861 --> 16:08.996
It's how you're choosing
to contextualize it

16:09.030 --> 16:11.198
that makes it appear
beyond a reasonable doubt.

16:11.232 --> 16:12.699
It's kind of like hearing hoofbeats

16:12.734 --> 16:14.635
and thinking horses, not zebras.

16:14.669 --> 16:16.036
With all due respect,

16:16.070 --> 16:18.038
we don't get a lot of
zebras around here.

16:18.072 --> 16:20.040
You seriously don't think
this man murdered his wife?

16:20.074 --> 16:23.210
I don't think he stabbed
her to death, no.

16:23.244 --> 16:26.046
But I think he might know who did.

16:26.080 --> 16:29.149
<i>[Ring]</i>

16:29.184 --> 16:31.618
<i>[Ring]</i>

16:31.653 --> 16:32.953
You said you lost your phone.

16:32.987 --> 16:34.121
Ray, you need to get my kids back

16:34.155 --> 16:34.988
from the cops, right now.

16:35.023 --> 16:37.024
There's nothin' I can do.
You know that.

16:37.058 --> 16:39.293
You bring them here and then,
we're getting out of town.

16:39.327 --> 16:40.827
I will not get railroaded into spending

16:40.862 --> 16:42.629
the rest of my life in a Mexican prison.

16:42.664 --> 16:43.897
Dan, what's wrong with you?

16:43.932 --> 16:46.066
The FBI is gonna clear you.

16:46.100 --> 16:48.035
You've got nothin' to
worry about, right?

16:48.069 --> 16:49.570
Get my damn kids back, Ray.

16:49.604 --> 16:51.371
[Chime]

16:51.406 --> 16:54.141
Look, I've gotta go. I'll be back.

16:54.175 --> 16:56.476
[Suspenseful music plays]

17:11.192 --> 17:12.992
[Tires screech]

17:17.267 --> 17:19.900
<i>¿Y dónde está? Pues encuéntralo.</i>

17:19.935 --> 17:21.135
<i>Daniel just took off.</i>

17:21.169 --> 17:22.637
And we lost him.

17:22.671 --> 17:24.137
What do you say now, Agent Garrett?

17:24.172 --> 17:26.874
I said Daniel didn't stab his wife.

17:26.907 --> 17:28.242
But he might have just reached out

17:28.277 --> 17:29.477
- [cellphone beeps]
- to the person who did.

17:29.511 --> 17:31.979
Monty, we got eyes on Daniel?

17:32.014 --> 17:34.749
As you predicted, he
reached out to his partner in crime.

17:34.783 --> 17:35.783
Here's a fun fact for you...

17:35.817 --> 17:38.953
Daniel's cellphone business
plan has four phones,

17:38.987 --> 17:40.621
two of which... thank you, GPS...

17:40.656 --> 17:42.790
are now moving together hand in hand.

17:42.824 --> 17:43.791
We're on our way.

17:43.825 --> 17:46.661
♪

17:46.695 --> 17:48.663
Monty, I need to know
where we're headed.

17:48.697 --> 17:52.233
They seem to have gotten a
room at the Rancho Sierra Inn.

17:52.267 --> 17:53.601
CI Ruiz,

17:53.635 --> 17:55.736
suspects are located at
the Rancho Sierra Inn.

17:55.771 --> 17:57.238
We will follow your tactical lead.

17:57.272 --> 17:58.239
Ruiz: Copy that.

17:58.273 --> 18:00.141
[Sirens wail]

18:06.548 --> 18:09.750
[Police radio chatter, dog barking]

18:09.785 --> 18:11.118
Can you pinpoint a location?

18:11.153 --> 18:14.355
Monty: Uh, they're
like 75 feet due east.

18:14.389 --> 18:16.624
Mae and I will cover the back.

18:25.200 --> 18:27.802
[Speaking Spanish]

18:27.836 --> 18:29.670
[Object shatters, body thuds]

18:32.641 --> 18:34.709
[Groans]

18:34.743 --> 18:37.078
[Window opens, dog barking]

18:41.416 --> 18:43.851
Get back in. Get down.

18:43.885 --> 18:45.052
Don't! Don't! Wait! Don't shoot!

18:45.087 --> 18:47.321
I surrender! I surrender.

18:47.356 --> 18:48.689
Clara: Daniel, you okay?

18:48.724 --> 18:49.690
Looks like she clocked you pretty good.

18:49.725 --> 18:50.991
Oh, yeah. My head.

18:51.026 --> 18:52.493
- Ah.
- Stand up.

18:52.527 --> 18:54.028
- Ah.
- Good.

18:54.062 --> 18:56.464
'Cause you're under arrest.

18:59.935 --> 19:03.371
Ruiz: <i>Since Puerto del Santos
doesn't have a police force,</i>

19:03.405 --> 19:05.139
<i>it also doesn't have a jail.</i>

19:05.173 --> 19:06.574
[Camera shutter clicks]

19:06.608 --> 19:09.009
<i>So, in order to look after
our new prisoners...</i>

19:09.044 --> 19:10.878
- [Camera shutter clicks]
- <i>We've had to make</i>

19:10.912 --> 19:14.348
<i>some special arrangements nearby.</i>

19:14.383 --> 19:16.384
<i>Playa Diablo Penitentiary.</i>

19:18.253 --> 19:20.221
<i>They say that even the devil himself</i>

19:20.255 --> 19:23.657
would prefer death over Diablo.

19:23.692 --> 19:25.893
Ruiz: Laura Hayes, Fort Worth, Texas.

19:25.927 --> 19:27.595
This says you're a promotions manager.

19:27.629 --> 19:28.929
Is that right?

19:28.964 --> 19:30.498
You ready to talk to us, Laura?

19:31.967 --> 19:34.535
What were you thinking,

19:34.569 --> 19:36.837
taking off and leaving your children?

19:36.872 --> 19:38.906
I wasn't leaving my children.

19:38.940 --> 19:41.075
I'd never abandon them.

19:41.109 --> 19:42.777
They're all I have left in this world.

19:42.811 --> 19:45.446
Let's talk about you and Daniel.

19:45.480 --> 19:47.248
How long were you guys having an affair?

19:47.282 --> 19:49.350
Two years, I guess.

19:49.384 --> 19:51.018
But I swear, at the
time when we started,

19:51.052 --> 19:52.052
I didn't know he was married.

19:52.087 --> 19:54.855
I wish I could go back and
make a different choice.

19:54.890 --> 19:56.690
At the time, I-I felt
like I needed more,

19:56.725 --> 19:57.691
like I deserved more.

19:57.726 --> 20:01.061
But you did find out he
was married eventually,

20:01.096 --> 20:02.296
- right?
- I did.

20:02.330 --> 20:05.032
His wife, she found out about
us around that same time, too.

20:05.066 --> 20:06.367
She filed for divorce.

20:06.401 --> 20:07.802
I begged her to reconsider,

20:07.836 --> 20:09.737
if not for us, for the
sake of the children.

20:09.771 --> 20:12.206
I told her I'd break it off, and I did.

20:12.240 --> 20:15.576
He comes to me and he says he
needs to fight for his family.

20:15.610 --> 20:16.710
All the promises,

20:16.745 --> 20:19.814
all the plans we made, just gone,

20:19.848 --> 20:21.382
thrown away like garbage.

20:21.416 --> 20:23.984
I shouldn't have lied to you before.

20:24.019 --> 20:25.619
I-I wasn't thinking straight.

20:25.654 --> 20:27.788
I thought I could talk to
Laura, convince her to...

20:27.823 --> 20:29.957
convince her to do what, Daniel?

20:29.991 --> 20:31.258
[Sighs]

20:31.293 --> 20:33.127
To tell the truth.

20:33.161 --> 20:34.495
Laura killed my wife.

20:34.529 --> 20:36.263
Clara: The car that you were driving

20:36.298 --> 20:38.799
was a rental car you
picked up in Fort Worth.

20:38.834 --> 20:44.171
So you drove 1,500 miles
to do what exactly?

20:44.206 --> 20:45.639
I don't know. I wanted
to come down here

20:45.674 --> 20:48.609
and blow up his life like he had mine.

20:48.643 --> 20:51.111
Phone records say you were
still in touch with Laura

20:51.146 --> 20:53.147
and that you gave her
one of your phones.

20:53.181 --> 20:54.982
I was still juggling.

20:55.016 --> 20:57.084
I was hoping this trip
would fix everything.

20:57.118 --> 20:58.986
Then Jessica found out
that Laura was calling me.

20:59.020 --> 21:00.821
What she didn't know is
that Laura had followed us

21:00.856 --> 21:01.856
all the way down here.

21:01.890 --> 21:03.157
Got a motel room,

21:03.191 --> 21:06.193
called Dan a few times,

21:06.228 --> 21:09.697
and then, around midnight,
I called one more time.

21:09.731 --> 21:10.764
You're gonna meet me.

21:10.799 --> 21:12.466
You're gonna meet me at
the boardwalk in an hour.

21:12.501 --> 21:13.968
I'm headed over there, okay?

21:14.002 --> 21:15.469
And I threatened him,

21:15.504 --> 21:18.606
told him I'd come over if
he didn't come see me.

21:18.640 --> 21:20.274
She wanted to meet me at the boardwalk.

21:20.308 --> 21:21.809
I didn't have a choice. I had to go.

21:22.978 --> 21:24.311
And when I hung up the phone,

21:24.346 --> 21:25.846
I caught my reflection in the mirror,

21:25.881 --> 21:28.349
and I didn't even recognize myself.

21:28.383 --> 21:30.885
I mean, how did I become
this crazy stalker?

21:30.919 --> 21:33.988
I felt so much guilt and shame.

21:34.022 --> 21:36.991
Wasn't even like I
decided not to see him.

21:37.025 --> 21:38.459
I just passed out.

21:38.493 --> 21:40.561
Laura never showed up. I called her.

21:40.595 --> 21:42.963
Never heard anything, so I
went back to the villa.

21:42.998 --> 21:44.999
What time was that?

21:45.033 --> 21:46.100
Quarter after 2:00 in the morning.

21:46.134 --> 21:49.703
And you didn't think to check
on Jessica at the time?

21:49.738 --> 21:51.639
I did. I checked the bedroom.

21:51.673 --> 21:54.041
The door was locked. I figured
she was pissed at me.

21:54.075 --> 21:55.709
I got up at 4:00 a.m. to check again.

21:55.744 --> 21:57.011
This time, the door was unlocked,

21:57.045 --> 21:57.912
and Jessica was gone.

21:57.946 --> 22:00.047
I might have been
jealous of that woman,

22:00.081 --> 22:01.081
but I didn't kill her.

22:01.116 --> 22:03.984
I swear I didn't kill my wife.

22:04.019 --> 22:07.221
But if you're asking me
if I think he did it,

22:07.255 --> 22:08.989
I will you tell you without hesitation

22:09.024 --> 22:10.658
that, Daniel,

22:10.692 --> 22:13.527
he's capable of anything
that helps Daniel.

22:13.562 --> 22:16.163
Laura knew exactly how this would look.

22:16.197 --> 22:18.032
She's been hell-bent on punishing me

22:18.066 --> 22:18.933
for what I did to her.

22:18.967 --> 22:20.868
And I don't know. Maybe I deserve it.

22:20.902 --> 22:23.904
But Megan and Ryan, they
don't deserve any of this.

22:23.939 --> 22:25.372
None of it.

22:29.044 --> 22:31.045
♪

22:40.822 --> 22:44.058
- [Sighs]
- What do you see here, Jack?

22:46.261 --> 22:49.063
Well, I'll tell you what I <i>don't</i> see.

22:49.097 --> 22:51.098
I don't see Daniel
stabbing his wife to death

22:51.132 --> 22:54.068
with his children only a few feet away.

22:54.102 --> 22:55.970
Early in my career, I
learned to see the scene

22:56.004 --> 22:56.904
as the killer does...

22:56.938 --> 22:59.273
at the same hour, under
the same conditions.

22:59.307 --> 23:00.574
And this doesn't add up.

23:00.609 --> 23:01.742
So you don't think he's lying now?

23:01.776 --> 23:02.743
I think his lies, at first,

23:02.777 --> 23:05.446
were meant to cover up
his affair with Laura.

23:05.480 --> 23:08.115
Then they continued out
of his sincere belief

23:08.149 --> 23:11.151
that she'd become the scorned
woman avenging her broken heart

23:11.186 --> 23:14.989
by killing his wife and
framing him for the murder.

23:15.023 --> 23:16.090
That may be what he believes,

23:16.124 --> 23:17.324
but that's not what happened.

23:17.359 --> 23:20.094
Even though her patterns suggest
an obsessive love disorder,

23:20.128 --> 23:23.063
her passions tend towards
deliberate self-harm

23:23.098 --> 23:24.431
rather than externalized rage.

23:24.466 --> 23:26.500
Plus, if she's not working with Daniel,

23:26.534 --> 23:29.103
she just wouldn't be capable of
wrapping up Jessica on her own,

23:29.137 --> 23:31.472
carrying her off the property,
then dumping her in the ocean.

23:31.506 --> 23:33.107
What about that insurance policy?

23:33.141 --> 23:35.409
Monty's initial information
came from the company

23:35.443 --> 23:36.944
that issued that policy,

23:36.978 --> 23:38.679
but Daniel's lawyer got me in touch

23:38.713 --> 23:40.147
with the Wolfs' estate planner.

23:40.181 --> 23:43.017
It was Jessica's idea to
purchase that policy.

23:43.051 --> 23:44.618
And that, my friends, is the sound

23:44.653 --> 23:46.120
of motive leaving the building.

23:46.154 --> 23:48.322
We've been looking at this
whole thing the wrong way

23:48.356 --> 23:49.590
from the beginning.

23:49.624 --> 23:51.158
Okay, so back to square one.

23:51.192 --> 23:52.693
Who killed Jessica Wolf and why?

23:52.727 --> 23:55.963
But now we have two innocent
Americans falsely accused

23:55.997 --> 23:58.298
and imprisoned for that crime,

23:58.333 --> 23:59.633
and we've got to get them out of there.

23:59.668 --> 24:00.834
♪

24:00.869 --> 24:02.803
You want me to release them?

24:02.837 --> 24:05.305
I'd like you to release
them into our custody,

24:05.340 --> 24:08.108
pending the outcome
of the investigation.

24:08.143 --> 24:10.144
Investigation's over. We got 'em.

24:10.178 --> 24:12.780
They didn't kill Jessica Wolf.

24:12.814 --> 24:13.981
How can you say that?

24:14.015 --> 24:16.784
Because you looked into their
eyes and saw their souls?

24:16.818 --> 24:19.019
Everything that's done
or left at a crime scene

24:19.054 --> 24:20.821
isn't just a piece of evidence.

24:20.855 --> 24:23.123
It's a piece of the offender himself.

24:23.158 --> 24:25.325
My team's job is to put
those pieces together,

24:25.360 --> 24:27.061
create a profile of that person.

24:27.095 --> 24:28.162
Yeah, in this case,

24:28.196 --> 24:30.898
that profile does not fit
Laura Hayes or Daniel Wolf.

24:30.932 --> 24:33.167
Your profile or wishful thinking?

24:33.201 --> 24:35.302
Because I also know it's your
job to protect Americans.

24:35.336 --> 24:39.673
Look, we're the ones extending
professional courtesy now.

24:39.708 --> 24:41.341
We can have the same conversation

24:41.376 --> 24:43.811
with your superiors in Mexico city.

24:43.845 --> 24:45.379
We could.

24:45.413 --> 24:47.214
But even if they agreed with you,

24:47.248 --> 24:48.215
it's out of their hands.

24:48.249 --> 24:50.317
The state prosecutor
will now decide the fate

24:50.351 --> 24:51.985
of Daniel Wolf and his mistress.

24:52.020 --> 24:54.188
There has to be at least
some way to transfer them

24:54.222 --> 24:55.222
out of Playa Diablo.

24:55.256 --> 24:56.223
No.

24:56.257 --> 24:57.124
In fact, in 24 hours,

24:57.158 --> 24:58.726
they'll be let into general population.

24:58.760 --> 25:00.494
That's like handing
them a death sentence.

25:00.528 --> 25:03.330
They say the punishment fits
the crime, Agent Garrett.

25:03.364 --> 25:05.499
But if you want to break them
out of jail, all you have to do

25:05.533 --> 25:08.368
is bring the prosecutor the real killer.

25:16.165 --> 25:17.298
Restarting this investigation

25:17.333 --> 25:19.967
without the MFP's cooperation
is gonna be challenging,

25:20.002 --> 25:21.736
- but, Mae, you say you have something.
- Yeah.

25:21.770 --> 25:23.471
So I've been trying to
track down those sheets

25:23.505 --> 25:24.238
- that were wrapped around the body.
- Mm-hmm.

25:24.273 --> 25:25.907
I assumed that they were bed sheets

25:25.941 --> 25:27.742
- that were taken from the villa.
- They weren't?

25:27.776 --> 25:30.311
No. A fancy place like this
keeps really tidy records,

25:30.346 --> 25:32.680
and all sheets and other sort
of linens are accounted for,

25:32.715 --> 25:35.750
which means that the killer
brought the sheets with him.

25:35.784 --> 25:36.617
Okay, so where are we

25:36.652 --> 25:38.820
on trace analysis from Jessica's body?

25:38.854 --> 25:39.987
I can head back to the plane

25:40.022 --> 25:41.456
and check on the presumptive reports.

25:41.490 --> 25:42.657
Go now.

25:42.691 --> 25:44.759
I need eyes in that prison just
in case the clock runs out.

25:44.793 --> 25:46.594
I agree. I'll see what I can do.

25:48.330 --> 25:49.864
That silhouette that Ryan thought

25:49.898 --> 25:51.199
was his father standing over him,

25:51.233 --> 25:52.867
do you think it's possible he saw

25:52.901 --> 25:54.035
something more than he remembers?

25:54.069 --> 25:55.136
I'm not sure.

25:55.170 --> 25:57.472
I need you to perform a
cognitive interview with him.

25:57.506 --> 25:58.773
Jack, what if Ryan doesn't remember

25:58.807 --> 26:00.975
because he suppressed that memory?

26:01.009 --> 26:03.177
- If we open that wound...
- We don't have a choice.

26:03.212 --> 26:04.512
I know it's terrible,

26:04.546 --> 26:06.280
but we need to do
everything we can right now

26:06.315 --> 26:07.515
to make sure that he and his sister

26:07.549 --> 26:08.616
don't lose their father, too.

26:11.553 --> 26:15.890
Now, I want you to feel
yourself floating backwards

26:15.924 --> 26:19.627
and feel yourself lying on the couch.

26:19.661 --> 26:21.562
My skin keeps sticking to it.

26:21.597 --> 26:23.898
It's warm.

26:23.932 --> 26:26.000
Air conditioner is off.

26:26.034 --> 26:28.903
And the air, what does it smell like?

26:28.937 --> 26:30.705
[Inhales deeply]

26:30.739 --> 26:31.906
Seaweed.

26:31.940 --> 26:34.742
F-fish and chicken from the barbecue.

26:34.777 --> 26:36.377
I want you to feel yourself

26:36.412 --> 26:38.713
as you were drifting
in and out of sleep,

26:38.747 --> 26:40.915
your eyes open.

26:40.949 --> 26:42.717
What do you see?

26:42.751 --> 26:47.221
I see my dad standing over me.

26:47.256 --> 26:49.991
I need you to take a closer look.

26:50.025 --> 26:51.893
Can you see his face?

26:51.927 --> 26:55.730
No, I can't, but I hear him.

26:55.764 --> 26:56.631
What do you hear?

26:56.665 --> 26:58.900
- [Indistinct whispering]
- He's whispering.

27:00.636 --> 27:03.237
He's holding a cross on a chain.

27:03.272 --> 27:05.106
- [Voice breaking]
- Why is he holding a cross?

27:05.140 --> 27:06.073
A cross?

27:06.108 --> 27:09.510
Like two ice cream
sticks crossed together,

27:09.545 --> 27:10.912
tied with gold.

27:10.946 --> 27:14.916
- [Woman screaming]
- And I hear my mom crying.

27:14.950 --> 27:16.350
I got to go to sleep.

27:16.385 --> 27:17.919
I got to go back to sleep.

27:17.953 --> 27:20.555
That's the man.

27:20.589 --> 27:22.557
That's the man who killed my mom.

27:22.591 --> 27:24.959
I should've woken up.
I could've saved her.

27:24.993 --> 27:26.060
- You need to let me go!
- No, no. No.

27:26.094 --> 27:27.361
Let me go!

27:27.396 --> 27:28.763
Stop. Look in my eyes.

27:28.797 --> 27:30.298
This is not your fault.

27:30.332 --> 27:31.766
There is nothing you could've done.

27:31.800 --> 27:33.768
- [Sniffles]
- Nothing. Okay?

27:33.802 --> 27:35.236
Do you understand?

27:35.270 --> 27:36.437
I'm so scared.

27:36.472 --> 27:38.906
Come here. It's okay.

27:40.008 --> 27:41.375
Look. You are safe.

27:41.410 --> 27:43.444
No one is gonna hurt you. Okay?

27:43.479 --> 27:45.513
[Slow piano music plays]

27:48.851 --> 27:50.885
[Woman singing in Spanish]

28:16.845 --> 28:19.647
[Ringing]

28:19.681 --> 28:20.548
Mae: Hey, Clara.

28:20.582 --> 28:21.682
Um, listen, you didn't happen to find

28:21.717 --> 28:24.485
any residue of protein filaments
on the body, did you?

28:24.520 --> 28:25.820
Mm, no. Why?

28:25.854 --> 28:26.787
I'm working on a theory.

28:26.822 --> 28:29.824
What about any hemp
fibers or mineral oils?

28:29.858 --> 28:31.993
It's like you're reading my
preliminary trace report.

28:32.027 --> 28:33.261
I'll be right over.

28:33.295 --> 28:35.930
You and Monty and the art skills.

28:35.964 --> 28:37.665
Monty is the artist. I just doodle.

28:37.699 --> 28:39.667
But these particular doodles

28:39.701 --> 28:40.735
suggest something peculiar to me.

28:40.769 --> 28:43.604
And if I'm right, what Ryan
saw in the killer's hand

28:43.639 --> 28:46.374
was a crude Latin blasphemy
of the True Cross.

28:46.408 --> 28:48.009
True Cross... what people refer to

28:48.043 --> 28:50.011
as the physical remnants of the cross

28:50.045 --> 28:51.879
- that Jesus was crucified on.
- Exactly.

28:51.914 --> 28:54.348
And in this theological
context, I was thinking

28:54.383 --> 28:56.017
about how the killer wrapped the body.

28:56.051 --> 28:58.119
What if he didn't do it as
a forensic countermeasure?

28:58.153 --> 28:59.854
What if he did it because
he was actually trying

28:59.888 --> 29:02.290
to mimic
an old-Judeo-Christian burial custom?

29:02.324 --> 29:03.558
You mean prepping the body with oil

29:03.592 --> 29:04.592
then shrouding it with cloth?

29:05.761 --> 29:07.128
Well, if that's true, then
we're not just talking

29:07.162 --> 29:08.629
about someone with remorse.

29:08.664 --> 29:09.697
We're talking about someone...

29:09.731 --> 29:11.299
someone with a signature.

29:11.333 --> 29:13.000
And I think this someone is caught

29:13.035 --> 29:14.569
between frenzied aggression,

29:14.603 --> 29:15.836
the multiple stab wounds,

29:15.871 --> 29:18.039
and a more serene, contemplative ritual

29:18.073 --> 29:19.840
- of preparing a body for burial.
- Yeah.

29:19.875 --> 29:20.908
But what we're actually talking about

29:20.943 --> 29:22.577
is burial in the ground rituals,

29:22.611 --> 29:25.313
- not dumped at sea like Jessica was.
- Yeah.

29:25.347 --> 29:27.014
Well, there's still a lot to fill in.

29:27.049 --> 29:29.750
But if we are right, this isn't
this unsub's first rodeo.

29:29.785 --> 29:31.018
Okay, well, I think that we should see

29:31.053 --> 29:32.153
what Monty can dig up.

29:32.187 --> 29:35.056
So I cross-referenced our
M.O's, and I got something...

29:35.090 --> 29:36.924
five more homicides taking place

29:36.959 --> 29:39.026
across these Latin-American resorts

29:39.061 --> 29:40.261
all over the last five years...

29:40.295 --> 29:43.064
all tourist families, all
taking place on the same day.

29:43.098 --> 29:46.233
Well, these victims were
male, teens and adolescents,

29:46.268 --> 29:48.936
the family's oldest male children.

29:48.971 --> 29:50.304
<i>Día de los Inocentes.</i>

29:51.440 --> 29:53.374
Jessica wasn't the unsub's target.

29:53.408 --> 29:55.176
Uh, excuse me?

29:55.210 --> 29:56.143
<i>Día de los Inocentes.</i>

29:56.178 --> 29:58.379
That is what all of this
means to the unsub.

29:58.413 --> 30:01.048
Wait. Our unsub's obsessed with
Mexico's April fools' day?

30:01.083 --> 30:04.452
Today, <i>Día de los Inocentes</i>
is an excuse to pull pranks.

30:04.486 --> 30:06.053
But it began hundreds of years ago

30:06.088 --> 30:07.688
as a feast day in remembrance

30:07.723 --> 30:10.224
of the biblical massacre of
the innocents by King Herod.

30:10.258 --> 30:12.627
Herod ordered the execution
of all male children under 2

30:12.661 --> 30:14.128
in the vicinity of Bethlehem

30:14.162 --> 30:15.630
so as to avoid loss of his throne

30:15.664 --> 30:16.797
to the coming Messiah.

30:16.832 --> 30:17.698
But if you're right,

30:17.733 --> 30:20.101
he's mixing up biblical
traditions here...

30:20.135 --> 30:21.569
the innocents and passover.

30:21.603 --> 30:23.070
And adapting his own narrative line.

30:23.105 --> 30:24.405
- Which is?
- I don't know.

30:24.439 --> 30:26.574
But I do know that Jessica was murdered

30:26.608 --> 30:28.042
because she walked in on the unsub

30:28.076 --> 30:30.044
as he was about to attack her son, Ryan.

30:31.413 --> 30:34.382
Jessica: Daniel. Daniel.

30:34.416 --> 30:35.750
[Gasps, muffled scream]

30:35.784 --> 30:37.652
All those defensive wounds.

30:37.686 --> 30:39.120
Jessica fought as hard as she could

30:39.154 --> 30:41.489
to protect her children.

30:41.523 --> 30:42.890
[Screaming]

30:42.924 --> 30:45.826
Ryan and these five other
boys are surrogates

30:45.861 --> 30:48.996
for whatever our unsub's
twisted fantasy is.

30:49.031 --> 30:51.165
Right, but if Ryan was
the real target here,

30:51.199 --> 30:52.333
then why didn't the unsub go after him

30:52.367 --> 30:54.435
after he finished with Jessica?

30:56.104 --> 30:57.605
Because Daniel came back.

30:57.639 --> 30:59.073
He interrupted him again.

30:59.107 --> 31:00.541
[Lock disengages]

31:03.545 --> 31:05.179
And he was already out
of his comfort zone,

31:05.213 --> 31:06.247
having killed Jessica.

31:06.281 --> 31:08.082
The only thing left to do
was clean up his tracks,

31:08.116 --> 31:09.183
confuse the crime scene.

31:09.217 --> 31:10.518
Okay. So let's draw it up.

31:10.552 --> 31:13.688
Our unsub is undoubtedly male.

31:13.722 --> 31:16.490
Given his technical proficiency
and historical knowledge,

31:16.525 --> 31:18.993
he is most likely in his 30s or 40s.

31:19.027 --> 31:21.629
Highly educated, and yet, due
to socialization issues,

31:21.663 --> 31:23.030
he's most likely a dropout

31:23.065 --> 31:25.700
or someone who was
expelled from college,

31:25.734 --> 31:27.301
maybe even a seminary or church.

31:27.335 --> 31:30.371
He is both motivated and
repelled by his concept of sin,

31:30.405 --> 31:33.674
which somehow correlates
to his chosen surrogates

31:33.709 --> 31:35.476
and suggests that he's a grief-induced,

31:35.510 --> 31:37.011
anger-retaliatory narcissist.

31:37.045 --> 31:38.946
You know, if this guy really thinks

31:38.980 --> 31:41.449
that he's some latter-day King
Herod massacring Messiahs,

31:41.483 --> 31:44.585
then maybe he's retaliating
against God himself.

31:45.687 --> 31:48.022
Which could mean our unsub's trigger

31:48.056 --> 31:50.558
was some kind of act of God,

31:50.592 --> 31:52.860
maybe even one that took
the life of a loved one.

31:52.894 --> 31:56.497
Monty, go back to just
prior to the first murder.

31:56.531 --> 31:59.567
Identify any natural
disasters in the region

31:59.601 --> 32:01.502
- that could fit our profile.
- [Keyboard clacking]

32:13.215 --> 32:15.216
[Speaks Spanish]

32:23.391 --> 32:25.392
♪

32:28.964 --> 32:30.097
I've got something on
our act-of-God search.

32:30.132 --> 32:31.999
Take a look.

32:32.033 --> 32:35.102
<i>La verdadera iglesia Fe,
the true faith church.</i>

32:35.137 --> 32:38.072
Part of it collapsed during
an earthquake 6 years ago.

32:38.106 --> 32:41.008
The head pastor's son, Matthew, died.

32:41.042 --> 32:41.909
He was only 12 years old.

32:41.943 --> 32:44.612
Yeah. Matthew's father
is Rafael Acosta.

32:44.646 --> 32:45.446
He's got a record.

32:45.480 --> 32:47.414
About 6 months after his son died,

32:47.449 --> 32:50.785
he was arrested at Mazatlan for
assaulting a 13-year-old boy.

32:50.819 --> 32:52.553
This guy can't still be
the pastor there, can he?

32:52.587 --> 32:55.422
I wouldn't think so, but I'm
not finding a great deal

32:55.457 --> 32:58.259
of information online about
the church's current staff.

32:58.293 --> 33:00.361
Well, if this Rafael Acosta's our guy,

33:00.395 --> 33:02.129
doesn't make any sense that his victims

33:02.164 --> 33:03.597
would be surrogates for his dead son.

33:03.632 --> 33:06.300
All right, so who do
the victims represent?

33:06.334 --> 33:09.136
Guess we'll just have to
ask Rafael Acosta himself.

33:09.171 --> 33:10.237
Let's start with this church.

33:10.272 --> 33:12.139
I actually have two locations
of interest for you.

33:12.174 --> 33:13.607
One is the church itself.

33:13.642 --> 33:15.142
The other is a condemned property

33:15.177 --> 33:16.577
that the church also owns,

33:16.611 --> 33:19.547
about 15 miles northwest
of Las Casitas resort.

33:19.581 --> 33:20.381
Divide and conquer.

33:20.415 --> 33:22.583
Simmons and Mae, you take the church.

33:22.617 --> 33:25.452
Clara and I will check out
this condemned property.

33:25.487 --> 33:26.787
Let's go.

33:26.822 --> 33:28.856
[Crow caws]

33:32.527 --> 33:34.562
♪

33:44.773 --> 33:46.807
Hello.

33:46.842 --> 33:49.009
[Crow caws]

33:49.044 --> 33:50.477
Man: <i>Hola.</i>

33:56.284 --> 33:57.618
<i>¿Qué tal?</i>

33:57.652 --> 33:59.820
<i>Hola.</i>

33:59.855 --> 34:01.889
Soy Officer Simmons y es Officer Jarvis.
Somos del FBI.

34:04.159 --> 34:06.460
Gracias, but I do speak English.

34:06.494 --> 34:07.661
I'm Reverend Esteban Soria.

34:07.696 --> 34:10.664
How can I be of service to the FBI?

34:10.699 --> 34:12.032
We're looking for one
of your pastors...

34:12.067 --> 34:13.534
Rafael Acosta.

34:13.568 --> 34:15.803
He hasn't been with us
for a few years now.

34:15.837 --> 34:17.438
We understand that he lost his son here

34:17.472 --> 34:18.105
during an earthquake.

34:18.139 --> 34:20.507
Yes. A terrible tragedy.

34:20.542 --> 34:23.210
But yet, strangely
coupled with a miracle.

34:23.245 --> 34:26.112
Miracle? What do you mean?

34:26.147 --> 34:27.614
There were two boys in the sanctuary

34:27.649 --> 34:29.315
that day that it collapsed...

34:29.351 --> 34:31.351
Matthew and this boy, uh, Bryant.

34:31.386 --> 34:34.822
He and his parents were visitors
from the U.S. just like you.

34:34.856 --> 34:37.291
When we dug through the
rubble, we pulled him out,

34:37.324 --> 34:38.993
and he was still alive.

34:39.027 --> 34:41.295
Do you recall how Rafael
responded to this miracle?

34:41.329 --> 34:43.530
He was never the same after that day.

34:43.565 --> 34:46.634
He was always unusually fierce
in his expression of faith,

34:46.668 --> 34:48.135
some thought too fierce.

34:48.168 --> 34:50.004
Do you remember his
last name, Bryant's?

34:50.038 --> 34:52.339
Ah, I believe it was Bryant Holt.

34:52.373 --> 34:54.675
Do you have any idea where we
might be able to find Rafael now?

34:54.708 --> 34:56.409
No, I'm sorry. I don't.

34:56.444 --> 34:58.178
Gracias, Reverendo.

34:58.213 --> 35:00.748
Local media Down Baja Way
is still pretty analog,

35:00.782 --> 35:03.484
but I found this in a
Ballard, Utah, paper.

35:03.518 --> 35:04.718
The victims are all surrogates

35:04.753 --> 35:06.320
for this miracle boy, Bryant Holt.

35:06.354 --> 35:08.255
Yeah, Rafael Acosta is avenging himself

35:08.290 --> 35:10.658
by massacring this
innocent over and over.

35:10.692 --> 35:12.293
And we still need to find him.

35:17.432 --> 35:19.466
[Crow caws]

35:23.471 --> 35:25.306
♪

35:26.041 --> 35:27.241
It's clear.

35:28.743 --> 35:30.444
He was definitely here recently.

35:30.478 --> 35:34.081
$4,000 worth of jewelry really
did mean nothing to him.

35:34.115 --> 35:35.616
That was just a way to throw us off.

35:35.650 --> 35:36.583
He had no way to know

35:36.618 --> 35:39.053
how much the Wolf family
drama would do that.

35:39.087 --> 35:41.388
So where does he go from here?

35:41.423 --> 35:42.456
You know, I keep trying to wrap my head

35:42.490 --> 35:44.391
around this unsub's patience,

35:44.426 --> 35:47.461
his devotion to the annual cycle.

35:47.495 --> 35:50.731
How does he sustain
himself over 365 days

35:50.765 --> 35:52.399
in between sacrificial killings?

35:52.434 --> 35:53.567
Maybe he's like Dennis Rader.

35:53.601 --> 35:55.302
Right. The BTK killer.

35:55.337 --> 35:57.905
Rader was able to soothe
his killing urges

35:57.939 --> 35:59.707
by becoming a compliance agent.

35:59.741 --> 36:02.276
Maybe our unsub pacified his urges

36:02.310 --> 36:05.079
by working a job with
strict responsibilities,

36:05.113 --> 36:08.382
like a civil servant
or a code enforcer.

36:10.852 --> 36:12.186
Security guard.

36:18.093 --> 36:20.094
[Conversing in Spanish]

36:28.370 --> 36:30.337
I'm sorry this hasn't
been easy for you,

36:30.372 --> 36:32.339
but this gentleman's gonna
drive you to the airport

36:32.374 --> 36:35.009
so you can get on a
plane and go back home.

36:35.043 --> 36:37.444
I know how much your
grandparents miss you.

36:37.479 --> 36:39.446
- Where's Agent Clara?
- [Cellphone rings]

36:39.481 --> 36:40.814
Look at that. Speak of the devil.

36:40.849 --> 36:43.751
FBI.

36:43.785 --> 36:46.320
Agent Garrett, I was
starting to miss you.

36:51.459 --> 36:53.127
Yeah, I can hold the children.

36:54.295 --> 36:55.029
- [Knife plunges]
- [Gasps]

36:55.063 --> 36:56.697
- Stop! Aah!
- Stop! Let her go!

36:56.731 --> 36:59.500
What are you doing? Stop! Stop!

36:59.534 --> 37:01.335
Stop!

37:01.369 --> 37:02.469
Don't do it! Stop!

37:02.504 --> 37:02.836
[Knife plunges]

37:26.041 --> 37:28.276
All right. He's got Ryan.
He's got a knife.

37:28.310 --> 37:30.078
He knows we're here, Jack. Be careful.

37:32.615 --> 37:35.350
[Chanting]

37:43.158 --> 37:45.927
- Mea culpa.
- Rafael?

37:49.164 --> 37:51.499
We know what happened to your son.

37:53.969 --> 37:57.038
We know what happened to Matthew.

37:59.642 --> 38:01.609
We're very sorry for your loss.

38:01.644 --> 38:03.778
You know nothing.

38:03.812 --> 38:06.781
God took my son. I take his.

38:06.815 --> 38:08.483
- An eye for an eye.
- Clara: Rafael, no.

38:08.517 --> 38:11.052
God took my husband.

38:13.088 --> 38:15.924
Rafael, I know exactly
what it feels like

38:15.958 --> 38:17.225
to be angry with God.

38:18.127 --> 38:23.965
My husband, Brad, he was...

38:23.999 --> 38:26.334
he was the love of my life,

38:26.368 --> 38:29.504
and God ripped him away from me.

38:29.538 --> 38:35.510
Afterwards, I was just
consumed with rage.

38:35.544 --> 38:37.312
I was his most faithful servant.

38:37.346 --> 38:38.947
[Panting]

38:38.981 --> 38:40.148
Why take my Matthew?

38:40.182 --> 38:44.319
I asked myself the exact same
question when I lost Brad.

38:44.353 --> 38:48.089
All of that pain, it is...

38:48.123 --> 38:49.991
it is overwhelming, isn't it?

38:50.025 --> 38:52.026
It burns.

38:52.061 --> 38:54.429
And that's why you felt the need

38:54.463 --> 38:56.998
to take the lives of those boys

38:57.032 --> 39:00.468
because each time you
took one from this world,

39:00.502 --> 39:02.437
you thought that it
would stop that pain.

39:02.471 --> 39:04.439
But it didn't, did it?

39:04.473 --> 39:07.141
All of these acts of vengeance,

39:07.176 --> 39:10.845
they do nothing to quell the
agony of Matthew's death.

39:10.879 --> 39:13.348
It's not fair.

39:13.382 --> 39:15.216
- Matthew was innocent.
- Yes.

39:15.250 --> 39:17.652
Yes, he was,

39:17.686 --> 39:20.188
just like Ryan, just
like that little boy

39:20.222 --> 39:22.290
that you are holding in
your arms right now.

39:22.324 --> 39:24.058
No. He's been chosen.

39:24.093 --> 39:26.461
Rafael, I want you to listen to me.

39:26.495 --> 39:28.162
Remember what it says in proverbs...

39:28.197 --> 39:32.200
"let not mercy and truth forsake thee.

39:32.234 --> 39:34.869
Bind them upon thy neck.

39:34.903 --> 39:38.740
Write them on the table
with your heart."

39:38.774 --> 39:43.011
Rafael, do you know why God
writes his words in your heart?

39:43.045 --> 39:45.646
So that when your heart breaks,

39:45.681 --> 39:48.316
his words, they fall in.

39:48.350 --> 39:50.351
[Sobbing]

40:02.464 --> 40:05.166
I'm forsaken.

40:05.200 --> 40:07.468
It's over, Rafael. Put
your hands on your head.

40:15.944 --> 40:17.245
- [Car door closes]
- Dad. Dad.

40:17.279 --> 40:19.047
[Sobbing]

40:20.983 --> 40:23.618
Oh, my babies. My babies, I missed you.

40:23.652 --> 40:25.586
You're a lucky man, Daniel.

40:25.621 --> 40:27.555
Not too many people
get a second chance,

40:27.589 --> 40:29.290
a shot at redemption.

40:29.324 --> 40:30.892
I'm not sure I deserve it,

40:30.926 --> 40:33.061
but maybe I got it because of my kids.

40:37.099 --> 40:39.100
♪

40:51.847 --> 40:55.049
- [Sighs]
- You did great work today.

40:56.652 --> 40:58.252
Thank you.

40:58.287 --> 40:59.620
But...

40:59.655 --> 41:00.488
But what?

41:02.591 --> 41:05.660
And I thought Brad had
a bad poker face.

41:05.694 --> 41:08.329
Yours is so much worse.

41:08.363 --> 41:09.664
Is that right?

41:09.698 --> 41:11.132
Yeah.

41:14.369 --> 41:17.105
You cut open a pretty deep scar today

41:17.139 --> 41:21.142
in order to talk down Rafael Acosta.

41:21.176 --> 41:23.344
Oh, believe me, I didn't want to.

41:23.378 --> 41:26.047
But there's nothing
else I could have done.

41:28.517 --> 41:31.486
You gonna be all right?

41:31.520 --> 41:33.254
You know, when Brad died,

41:33.288 --> 41:36.157
it dawned on me for the very first time

41:36.191 --> 41:39.260
why every orthodox faith on this planet

41:39.294 --> 41:42.363
has these strict timelines and rituals

41:42.397 --> 41:45.266
for how you're supposed
to mourn the dead

41:45.300 --> 41:48.769
and move on with the living.

41:48.804 --> 41:53.307
You violate those customs,
you dishonor the dead.

41:53.342 --> 41:55.877
As well as the living.

41:55.911 --> 41:59.647
There has to be a time to grieve.

41:59.681 --> 42:01.983
And a time to move on.

42:04.186 --> 42:05.786
I'm really glad you're back.

42:07.022 --> 42:09.557
Me, too.

42:09.591 --> 42:11.192
So let's go home.

